# Interface for Agents

## Procurement primitives

Instead of messy websites, agents get structured actions:

- Search vendors
- Compare options
- Check company policy
- Request approval
- Execute payment
- Write purchase reason
- Store receipt
- Learn from past approvals/rejections

**Goal**: Reduce token usage via minimal, human-synced UI.

Note: (5:45–6:15) “This list is my core design decision. I researched agent token waste and built primitives to cut context length dramatically.”

